{"award_age":51.0,"bio_image":"full\/7f61b9b39b232188b01f7be41ef911dd86d7c33e.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1921-08-23T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/9\/9d\/Kenneth_Arrow%2C_Stanford_University.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kenneth_J._Arrow","mini_bio":"<p><b>Kenneth Joseph \"Ken\" Arrow<\/b> (born August 23, 1921) is an American economist, writer, and political theorist. He is the joint winner of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economics\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economics<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Hicks\" title=\"John Hicks\">John Hicks<\/a> in 1972. To date, he is the youngest person to have received this award, at 51.<\/p><p>In economics, he is a figure in post-World War II <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Neo-classical_economics\" title=\"Neo-classical economics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">neo-classical economic theory<\/a>. Many of his former graduate students have gone on to win the Nobel Memorial Prize themselves. His most significant works are his contributions to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Social_choice_theory\" title=\"Social choice theory\">social choice theory<\/a>, notably \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Arrow%27s_impossibility_theorem\" title=\"Arrow's impossibility theorem\">Arrow's impossibility theorem<\/a>\", and his work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/General_equilibrium\" title=\"General equilibrium\" class=\"mw-redirect\">general equilibrium<\/a> analysis. He has also provided foundational work in many other areas of economics, including <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Endogenous_growth_theory\" title=\"Endogenous growth theory\">endogenous growth theory<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Asymmetric_information\" title=\"Asymmetric information\" class=\"mw-redirect\">the economics of information<\/a>.<\/p><p>Arrow remains active on the international scene through a variety of initiatives including trustee of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economists_for_Peace_and_Security\" title=\"Economists for Peace and Security\">Economists for Peace and Security<\/a> and a member of the Advisory Board of Incentives for Global Health, the not-for-profit behind the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Health_Impact_Fund\" title=\"Health Impact Fund\">Health Impact Fund<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Kenneth J. Arrow","place_of_birth":"New York City","place_of_death":null,"text":"Kenneth J. Arrow , Economics, 1972","year":1972.0}